	<feedback mode="101" id="1">
		<paragraph x="0" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000">Otherwise you may not be answering the question correctly. Underline the keywords of the task and make sure you are clear about what kind of composition it is.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
	</feedback>
	<feedback mode="101" id="3">
		<paragraph x="0" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000">It's worth spending a few minutes to make a plan. Examiners expect to read a well organised composition that presents a logical, clearly developed argument.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
	</feedback>
	<feedback mode="101" id="4">
		<paragraph x="0" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000">If you don't do this you may find yourself searching for ideas halfway through writing. Or even worse, a great idea for the second paragraph may come to you while you've just finishing the conclusion...and then it's too late!</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
	</feedback>
	<feedback mode="101" id="5">
		<paragraph x="0" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000">You are not expected to write as an expert. Task 2 can be answered by anyone with a reasonable level of general knowledge, personal opinions on a wide range of subjects and good organisational skills as a writer.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
	</feedback>
	<feedback mode="101" id="6">
		<paragraph x="0" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000">This will result in a very badly organised composition. Plan first, then write.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
	</feedback>
	<feedback mode="101" id="7">
		<paragraph x="0" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000">Always give yourself a few minutes at the end to read through and check for careless mistakes, even if you haven't quite finished writing. </FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
	</feedback>
	<feedback mode="101" id="8">
		<paragraph x="0" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000">This is a waste of time and words.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
	</feedback>
	<feedback mode="101" id="9">
		<paragraph x="0" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000">Remember that examples give substance to your arguments. </FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
	</feedback>
	<feedback mode="101" id="11">
		<paragraph x="0" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000">You don't have time or enough words to do this. Anyway, not all the points will be worth mentioning. Choose the most important.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
	</feedback>
	<feedback mode="101" id="13">
		<paragraph x="0" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000">It's good to do this in order to make sure that you are answering the question. Keep the keywords of the task in your mind while you're writing.</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
	</feedback>
	<feedback mode="101" id="14">
		<paragraph x="0" y="+0" width="407" height="0" style="normal" tabs="" indent="0"><![CDATA[<TEXTFORMAT LEADING="2"><P ALIGN="LEFT"><FONT FACE="Verdana" SIZE="13" COLOR="#000000">Be careful about this. It's very easy to think that you are answering the question when in fact you are writing things which are not relevant. Don't include things that you happen to know about the subject simply because they are interesting facts. Ask yourself, 'am I answering the questions ?'</FONT></P></TEXTFORMAT>]]></paragraph>
